Objective:  
This project focuses on building a Programme GPA Calculator and PISS Management System. 
The system will have a web interface connected to a database. It should store and manage data 
for students, programmes, PISS, courses, grades, GPA, and target GPA calculations. The system 
will be developed specifically for the CSE and CIT programmes only. Users should be able to 
calculate their current GPA and determine what grades are needed to reach a target GPA. A super 
user should be able to add and manage programme structures and PISS records. This project 
should be done in groups of 6.  
Project Tasks:  
1. Entities and Attributes 
Identify the entities needed for the system. Create a total of nine entities. Each entity should have 
at least six attributes. Each entity must include a primary key. Use foreign keys to show 
relationships where needed. 
2. Normalization 
Normalize the database to third Normal Form (3NF). Show the steps from UNF to 1NF, then to 
2NF. Remove repeating data. Ensure all attributes depend on the full primary key. Use sample 
data to show each stage. 
3. ERD 
Create an ERD using Crow’s Foot notation. Show all entities and attributes. Clearly label 
primary and foreign keys. Show relationships and cardinalities. 
4. Sample Data 
Add at least three users to each table. Use realistic data. Include data for students, programmes 
(CSE and CIT only), PISS, courses, grades, GPA, and target GPA requests. 
5. Queries 
Write SQL queries to retrieve data. Include: 
● one-table query 
● join query using two or more tables 
● GPA calculation query 
● target GPA calculation query 
6. Stored Procedures 
Create at least two stored procedures. 
7. Trigger 
Create at least one trigger. The trigger should automate a task. For example, it may update the 
GPA record when a grade is added. Include the SQL code and a short explanation. 
8. Web Development 
Build a web dashboard using PHP and MySQL. 
The system should include: 
● signup 
● login 
● logout 
● restricted access 
Show the logged-in username on each page. 
The GPA features should allow users to: 
● enter grades 
● calculate GPA 
● enter a target GPA 
● calculate required grades 
All forms should validate input. Protect the system from SQL injection using prepared 
statements.  
